article.headline: Belmont 88, East Tenn. St. 85 (OT)
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Josh Goodwin scored a career-high 39 points and Justin Hare hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer to force overtime in Belmont's 88-85 win over ETSU Thursday night. Belmont (3-1, 1-0 Atlantic Sun Conference) had an 11-3 run in the last 42 seconds, including a 3-pointer from Goodwin, to pull back from an eight-point deficit and set up for Hare, who had been 0 for 6 from the arc. Goodwin, a junior guard, also broke an A-Sun record for 3-pointers with 11 made. ETSU (1-3, 0-1) led the whole game, except for when the Bruins pulled ahead with 3:14 left in overtime. The Buccaneers were led by Tim Smith with 21 points, Dillion Sneed with 17 and Brad Nuckles with 16. In the second half, the Bucs led 63-54 with 7:33 left when Belmont began its comeback with a 14-6 run to make it 71-68 with 1:37 remaining. ETSU got a pair of free throws from both Ben Rhoda and Nuckles to make it 75-68. Following a 1-of-2 trip to the line for Hare, Smith sank two free throws to make it 77-69 ETSU with 42 seconds remaining. In overtime, the Bruins scored on three points from Boomer Herndon, a 3-pointer from Andy Wicke and a field goal from Hare. Belmont outrebounded ETSU 52-47, led by Herdon with 12.
